	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64286132">Not in the US. At this point in the US most jobs are at-will. Which means that the company has zero obligations to the employee and vice versa. Either party can wake up one morning and decide to terminate the relationship and no need to state the reason why. Despite how bad this sounds it works out fairly well. A lot of employee-employee relationships will last for years or decades.</div>
	</div>

